**10. Technical Direction**

Note: Full technical decisions will be documented in a separate
Architecture Decision Record (ADR). This section captures directional
decisions relevant to product scope.

**10.1 Stack Considerations**

  ------------------- ----------------------------------------------------
  **Frontend**        React (web) + React Native or Expo (mobile). Single
                      codebase priority given small team and AI-assisted
                      development.

  **Backend**         Node.js or Python (FastAPI). REST API with GraphQL
                      consideration for graph queries.

  **Database ---      Graph DB (Neo4j or AWS Neptune) for the relationship
  Relationships**     layer --- the family graph is the core data
                      structure and warrants native graph storage.

  **Database ---      PostgreSQL for events, RSVPs, user accounts,
  Transactional**     notifications, and all transactional data.

  **Auth**            Clerk or Auth0 --- do not build authentication from
                      scratch. Social OAuth (Google, Apple) is required.

  **Media Storage**   Cloudflare R2 or AWS S3 for photo/media storage
                      (Phase 2).

  **Notifications**   SendGrid (email) + Twilio (SMS) + Firebase Cloud
                      Messaging (push). All three required at MVP.

  **Hosting**         Vercel (frontend) + Railway or Render (backend) for
                      MVP simplicity. Migrate to AWS/GCP at scale.

  **Chat (Phase 2)**  Stream.io --- do not build real-time messaging from
                      scratch.
  ------------------- ----------------------------------------------------

**10.2 Critical Technical Constraints**

-   Guest participation (no account required) must be architected from
    day one. This affects auth, session management, and data access
    patterns throughout the stack.

-   The privacy model must be enforced at the data layer --- not just
    the UI. Row-level security or equivalent is required from the start.

-   COPPA compliance for minor profiles must be designed in from the
    beginning. Parent-controlled minor profiles require special handling
    in auth and data access.

-   SMS and email delivery reliability is a product-critical dependency.
    Vendor SLA and deliverability must be evaluated before launch.

